---
alwaysApply: true
---

project:
name: accomtz
description: >
REST API backend for Accomtz property booking app.
Handles authentication, property management, booking logic,
and agent verification. Built with Node.js, Express, MongoDB Atlas,
and Cloudinary.

tech_stack:

- Node.js
- Express
- javascript
- MongoDB Atlas (Mongoose)
- Cloudinary
- JWT Authentication
- Multer for uploads

conventions:

- Use plain javascript everywhere .
- Use async/await in all controller functions.
- Separate logic into routes, controllers, and services.
- Use proper HTTP codes (200, 400, 401, 404, 500).
- Use ESLint + Prettier for formatting and linting.
- Use `dotenv` for all environment variables.
- Always return JSON responses with `{ success, message, data }` format.

folder_structure:

- src/
  - config/
  - controllers/
  - middleware/
  - models/
  - routes/
  - utils/
  - server.js

libraries:

- express
- mongoose
- jsonwebtoken
- bcryptjs
- multer
- cloudinary
- cors
- dotenv

ai_rules:

- When generating routes, use `Router()` and export default.
- Always define TypeScript interfaces for MongoDB models.
- Implement authentication via middleware using JWT.
- When uploading files, integrate with Cloudinary.
- Always validate inputs (e.g., name, email, password).
- Prefer modular imports, avoid mixing logic.
- Use `try/catch` around async functions with proper error handling.
